-- Megafon and Rostelecom to Get 4G for Olympics, Vedomosti Reports
-- B y   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 2012-03-14T04:41:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-14/megafon-and-rostelecom-to-get-4g-for-olympics-vedomosti-reports.html
Russia will give mobile phone
operators OAO Rostelecom and OAO MegaFon 4G frequencies for the
2014 Winter Olympics in the southern city of Sochi,  Vedomosti 
said, citing unidentified people familiar with the situation.  A government commission on radio frequencies will grant the
rights at a March 16 meeting, Vedomosti said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Bierman in Moscow at 
 sbierman1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
